    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "PHP Close File - fclose()",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The fclose() function is used to close an open file.",
      "html": "<p>The <code>fclose()</code> function is used to close an open file.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "It's a good programming practice to close all files after you have finished with them. You don't want an open file running around on your server taking up resources!",
      "html": "<p>It's a good programming practice to close all files after you have finished with them. \nYou don't want an open file running around on your \nserver taking up resources!</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The fclose() requires the name of the file (or a variable that holds the filename) we want to close:",
      "html": "<p>The <code>fclose()</code> requires the name of the file (or a variable that holds the \nfilename) we want to close:</p>"
    },
